Dear Hiring Team,

I am applying for the *Software Engineer II* role at *Versant* because the work closely matches what I have been building: internal platform tools, backend services, REST APIs, and production automation that improve developer productivity. At Sperse, I built a *React*, *Next.js*, and *TypeScript* internal platform tool for agent operations, developed *FastAPI*, *LangGraph*, and *LangChain* backend services, *REST APIs*, and data models for a multi-agent CRM platform, and created a *FastMCP* server with 160+ backend actions, validation, logging, metrics, monitoring, and *OpenTelemetry* instrumentation. I also automated daily PR triage with *OpenAI Codex* and a custom Bitbucket MCP server, wiring the review loop into *GitHub Actions* *CI/CD* checks that flagged latency, accuracy, and safety regressions before production.

Before that, at Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* with *PostgreSQL* and *Redis* that handled file uploads, downloads, and deletions across *S3*, *Google Cloud Storage*, and *MinIO* via expiring signed URLs. I also reduced query latency by optimizing *PostgreSQL* databases with window functions, materialized views, and indexes, then exposed the data through interactive *React* visualizations for business stakeholders. Those projects sharpened the kind of disciplined engineering I expect to bring to a team that builds reliable internal tooling, supports healthy production environments, and keeps improving the systems other engineers depend on every day.

VERSANT's mission to bring together bold ideas and iconic brands to shape the future of media, paired with values like trust, teamwork, and transparency, is the kind of environment I want to contribute to. The Platform Operations team's focus on helping engineers ship and operate software more efficiently aligns directly with my background in internal tooling, observability, and CI/CD-driven delivery with platform and SRE partners. I would welcome the opportunity to help *Versant* build the platforms that support Fandango, Rotten Tomatoes, and Fandango at Home.

I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

